			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>One of the services we offer to our partners is inclusion on the SGN GameBar, which helps users find new games to play. Recently we came out with a new version that has performed much better than our first iteration, and we are very happy with both the design and the results. Here&#8217;s a screenshot:</p>
<p><img border="0" width="587" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3122/2446444310_1aa60f4691_o.jpg" alt="SGN Social GameBar" height="84" /></p>
<p>There are a lot of cool things about this bar; it&#8217;s customizable (we currently have light and dark versions), it shows what your friends are playing (hence, the &#8220;much more social&#8221;), and it&#8217;s still not intrusive (though it does catch your eye). Implementing the bar in your games puts you on the map to get new users every day. To make it happen, check out the documentation on our <a href="http://developers.socialgn.com/the_sgn_api_documentation.php">API Documentation page</a> or included with the <a href="http://developers.socialgn.com/the_sgn_api_client_libraries.php">client download of your choice</a>.</p>
<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/sgndeveloper/~4/358818734" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
