		<description><![CDATA[Over the weekend, we quietly released a new version of the SGN Developer application on Facebook. This release has a lot of new features and improvements, so I think it&#8217;s a good idea for me to explain them here.
The first major improvement is the new registration form:

This version is as simple as can be. All [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Over the weekend, we quietly released a new version of the <a href="http://apps.facebook.com/sgndeveloper/">SGN Developer application on Facebook</a>. This release has a lot of new features and improvements, so I think it&#8217;s a good idea for me to explain them here.</p>
<p>The first major improvement is the new registration form:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thephotoherald/2379078008/" title="Latest SGN Developer app registration form by montoya.christian, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2042/2379078008_1e1a374441_o.png" alt="Latest SGN Developer app registration form" height="331" width="400" /></a></p>
<p>This version is as simple as can be. All you have to do is enter the Facebook app ID for your game and your e-mail address, along with the four optional &#8220;game stat names,&#8221; and we will pull all the relevant data from Facebook to register your application. We hope this makes the registration process as simple and error-free as possible for everyone.</p>
<p>The next major improvement is the &#8220;view games&#8221; page:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thephotoherald/2379150798/" title="SGN Developer &quot;my games&quot; stats view by montoya.christian, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2243/2379150798_8a00b5b341_o.png" width="399" height="419" alt="SGN Developer &quot;my games&quot; stats view" /></a></p>
<p>You can see here that we have comparative bar graphs for the clicks in / clicks out SGN GameBar metrics. This should help developers determine how their games are faring in terms of clicks given/received. We&#8217;ll have more stats available soon.</p>
<p>Another big improvement is the editing interface, which can be done from the same page:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thephotoherald/2378320991/" title="SGN Developer editing interface by montoya.christian, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2368/2378320991_29c9a8b8b9_o.png" width="399" height="266" alt="SGN Developer editing interface" /></a></p>
<p>I&#8217;ll have more information soon about the &#8220;Templates&#8221; tab. </p>
<p>Aside from all these interface improvements, we&#8217;ve also set this application up so that games will get automatic e-mails when they are approved or denied, and every denial will come with a reason to help developers get there games approved the next time they submit. </p>
<p>I hope developers will find this new interface much easier to use and I encourage everyone to submit their games right away! <a href="http://apps.facebook.com/sgndeveloper/">Check out the SGN Developer application here</a>.</p>
<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/sgndeveloper/~4/358818735" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
