			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This past week we implemented the SGN Platform GameBar. This is a game-centric exchange and is available to all games that are approved for the platform. <a href="http://developers.socialgn.com/the_sgn_link_exchange_documentation.php">The full documentation is here. </a></p>
<p>The SGN GameBar is far more effective than typical advertising methods; with a low footprint and the SGN brand value, it has the potential to drive valuable traffic to any game that&#8217;s included. It works on a merit system; a game has to implement and include the bar to be featured across other games. Other than that, there are no restrictions; it&#8217;s opt-in and developers can leave at any time&#8230; but why would anyone want to leave? <img src='http://blog.sgn.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /></p>
<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/sgndeveloper/~4/358818738" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
